f=Engineering/nova/operational/agent/nova-config.md · p=Machine-readable configuration nova, mobile builder. defining field `mobile_active` false default, false means nova entirely dormant. · h2:Config Template=`# --- The dormant switch (checked before everything) --- \· mobile_active: false                    # DEFAULT false. true only when the business has a mobile app. \· # false → nova dormant; all mobile triggers route to mia (web) \·  \· # --- Charter (senior authority) ---` · in=**`mobile_active: false` (default) nova dormant.** architecture, builds, releases; mobile request routes mia "web-only" note. operator flips true real app exists (tempo's pattern). `security_charter_path` most-restrictive; regardless, signing secrets operator-held nova runs data changes (Rail 3). `device_matrix` unset verification uses widest real devices available, labeled; never simulator-only verdict. `staged_rollout` rollback substitute mobile can't recalled; non-staged full release refused. `kill_switch` (raj feature flags) real mobile safety net; risky release without one finding. · f=Default state dormant. active, unfilled config degrades loudly; signing stays operator-held rollout stays staged two non-negotiables given mobile's weak rollback.